    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Optimization Helper - Graphic Design\r\n\r\n#### Instructions:\r\n\r\nA graphic designer notices their image editing software becomes slower the longer it runs, and eventually, it crashes after working on a large file for several hours. What would you suggest they do?\r\n\r\n#### Do This:\r\n1. Choose 2 or 3 actions from the list of **Possible Actions** below.\r\n2. Use AI Chat to compare the actions you selected and explain which is best.\r\n\r\n---\r\n::: details [**Possible Actions:**]\r\n1. Save the project and restart the application periodically to free up memory.\r\n2.\tCheck for updates or patches for the image editing software.\r\n3.\tMonitor memory usage with Task Manager while using the software.\r\n4.\tReduce the number of open projects or layers in the software.\r\n5.\tAllocate more virtual memory (swap space) on the computer.\r\n6.\tClose unnecessary background applications to free up system resources.\r\n7.\tUse a different image editing application optimized for large files.\r\n8.\tIncrease the resolution of the project file for better quality.\t\r\n9.\tInstall an older version of the software to see if the issue persists.\r\n10.\tDisable auto-save or other memory-intensive features in the software.\r\n11.\tInstall an antivirus program and run a full system scan.\r\n12.\tMove the project file to an external drive to free up internal storage.\r\n13.\tDisconnect the computer from the internet while working.\r\n14.\tOpen additional applications to “balance” the system resources.\r\n15.\tIncrease the priority of the editing software in Task Manager.\r\n:::",
